<task id="installation-instructions-windows" >
    <title>Install using the Windows installer</title>

  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords><indexterm>Installation <indexterm>Windows installation</indexterm></indexterm></keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  
    <taskbody>
      <context>To install <ph keyref="product"/> using the Windows installer:</context>
         
         
        <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Make sure that your system meets the system requirements listed above.</cmd>
      </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Download the Windows installer.</cmd>
            </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Validate the integrity of the downloaded file by <xref
            href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Md5sum" format="html" scope="external">checking it
            against the MD5 sum</xref> published on the download page. </cmd>
      </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Run the installer and follow the instructions in the installation program. </cmd>
            </step>

      <step>
        <cmd><?oxy_comment_start author="Mark" timestamp="20140730T171953-0400" comment="Presumably the way you start Oxygen and the way you enter your license is different when it is installed on a server. How is it done in these cases?"?><?oxy_comment_start author="bogdan" timestamp="20140731T164154+0300" comment="Server installation is identical. License registration differs only when dealing with a very large pool of users. In this case the license key can be injected in the installation folder in a file named &quot;licensekey.txt&quot;. The whole procedure is already described in the UserGuide (topic &quot;Named User License Registration with Text File&quot;)." mid="1"?>Start<?oxy_comment_end?><?oxy_comment_end mid="1"?>
          <ph keyref="product"/> using one of the following methods:</cmd>
        <choices id="choices_wlz_zrk_x4">
          <choice>Using one of the shortcuts created by the installer. </choice>
          <choice>By running <ph product="editor"><filepath>oxygen.bat</filepath></ph><ph
              product="author"><filepath>oxygenAuthor.bat</filepath></ph><ph product="developer"
                ><filepath>oxygenDeveloper.bat</filepath></ph><ph product="svnClient"
                ><filepath>syncroSVNClient.bat</filepath></ph>, which is located in the install
            folder. </choice>
        </choices>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>To license your copy of <ph keyref="product"/> go to <menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Help</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Register...</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> and enter your <xref keyref="install.license-key">license key</xref>.</cmd>
      </step>
        </steps>    </taskbody>
</task>
